If it can't, it should fallback to a RO role.


Disk compaction

VHD Disk compaction is a process that runs every time a user sign out. The compaction process is designed to automatically decrease the amount of storage a user's container, depending on a predefined threshold.

VHD Disk compaction is enabled by default, if you want to disable it.,

Dependency

VHD Disk compaction depends on optimize Drives service (defragsvc)

Requirements of Disk Compaction

Use dynamically expanding Virtual hard disk (VHDX) fixed size Virtual hard disk cannot be compacted.

disk compaction should be enabled (default it is enabled)

Size of the container must be greater than 1GB (size on disk).

FSLogix Workflow / connectionflow

User logs in to the Windows Machine with FSLogix installed and configured.

If the user has correct permission (Read/write), FSLogix Agents reads through the FSLogix configuration and checks VHD location.

If the user has correct permission (Read/write), the VHD(x) is dynamically attached/mounted to the machine.

The user profile is immediately available and appears in the system and behaves like a local profile.

After user logout the VHD is detached / unmounted gracefully ready to be attached the next time user logs in

